{
  "text": "On this task, many caudate neurons show reward-dependent modulation of target-related activity, which may reflect their roles in implementing selection [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] . For example, the neuron in Figure 1B was activated more by target presentation at the right than the left [CITATION_6] . In addition, for the same right target presentation, its response was further augmented if the right target is associated with the large reward. This target-direction dependent modulation in activity is observed in around 15% of analyzed caudate neurons [CITATION_7] . Such activity may confer useful information for selection based on the ''value'' of the targets.",
